Internet subscription in Nigeria has suddenly become a necessity for many, thanks to the increasing number of internet users in the country. According to a recent report by NCC, the number of internet subscribers in Nigeria currently stands at 122,489, 257 as of November 2019. Despite the growing competition among internet service providers, 9Mobile has proven to be the preferred choice for many subscribers. The network also recently reviewed its data packages to offer the best value across the industry in terms of both data volume and price.  Below is a table that compares 9mobile data offerings to that of MTN, Airtel, and Glo. The grids present the monthly, weekly, and daily subscription rates for the respective networks. Monthly Plans 9mobile Airtel GLO MTN 75GB 15,000 15,000 15,000 63GB 20,000 50GB 18,000 40GB 10,000 10,000 10,000 26GB 10,000 20GB 8,000 6,000 15GB 5,000 5,000 5,000 12.5GB 5,000 11GB 4,000 4,000 10GB 4,000 3,500 8GB 3,000 3,000 7GB 3,000 6GB 2,500 2,500 5.75GB 2,500 4.5GB 2,000 2,000 2,000  Taking a close look at the above table for monthly data subscription, it is not so hard to tell that 9mobile, MTN and Airtel share a lot in common, although, 9mobile offers more with its fast and efficient internet connectivity. For weekly data subscription, Airtel and MTN appear to offer the most options; however, 9mobile and Glo lead the pack as they offer more value for less spend; this is another benefit that 9mobile provides to its customers- ‘more value for less spend.’  Weekly 9Mobile Airtel GLO MTN 7GB 1,500 6.5GB 1,500 6GB 1,500 1,500 2GB 1GB 500 500 500 750MB 500 500 350MB 300 300  9mobile also wins the league for daily plans as it offers more value for less spend, especially as it offers more validity period for data usage. As seen in the table below, 9mobile subscribers can enjoy a 2GB subscription for 3-days, where other network providers offer the same for two days or even lesser. 9mobile also provides two options for its 1GB daily subscription, 